Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn only every couple of mins - this will result in the courgette picking up some nice colour.

Once cooked, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then transfer to a #bowl{}.

Return the (now empty) frying pan to medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @chorizo{90%g} and onion. Stir-fry until the chorizo starts to brown and the onion has softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the mushrooms and fry until starting to brown, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}, then stir in the @finely chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @tomato puree{30%g}, @Italian style herbs{1%tsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{75%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts).

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{7-8%minutes}.

While the sauce simmers, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Drain the @mozzarella{1}(drained and torn into small pieces).

Once everything's ready, stir the roasted aubergine, pepper, charred courgette and cooked penne into the sauce. Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed.

Transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the mozzarella and Cheddar.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the cheese is bubbling and golden brown, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Once the pasta bake's ready, spoon into your serving bowls and tuck in. Enjoy!